    <prj:ScienceGoal mode="Standard">
        <prj:name>Mapping the kinematics and fragmentation of massive infrared dark hubs</prj:name>
        <prj:note>The goal here is to perform a first test of the universality of the clump-fed scenario of massive star formation through the characterization of the kinematics and fragmentation of a sample of 5 infrared dark hubs. We propose to mosaic them all in band 3 using the compact configuration of the 12m array providing enough angular resolution to resolve individual filaments. In addition, we require ACA and TP observations as a consequence of the extended (&gt;1arcmin) nature of the dense gas emssion in these clouds. 
</prj:note>
